The paper discusses resource allocation in communication networks and smart grids, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY) communities. The paper also introduces a new framework for network utility maximization, which is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes an online algorithm, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
